:0.000589522745838091,u:"../Content/api-guide/Creating-a-Multiple-Device.htm",a:"This REST call supports opening object change requests where objects from multiple devices are being changed. FireFlow validates the API to ensure that mandatory elements are in place, such as permissions, template, date formats, that any specified device exists in AFA, and so on. The change request ...",t:"Create a multiple device object change request"},"483":{i:0.00392985124439706,u:"../Content/api-guide/rule-removal-change-request.htm",a:"The ruleRemovalChangeRequest creates a FireFlow change request to remove or disable a device rule, using the rule removal workflow.  FireFlow validates the API to ensure that mandatory elements are in place, such as permissions, template, date formats, and that any specified device exists in AFA. ...",t:"Create a rule removal change request"},"484":{i:0.000589522745838091,u:"../Content/api-guide/updatetrafficchangerequestscustomfields_request1.htm",a:"The FireFlow REST API updates a Traffic Change Request\u0027s Custom Fields. FireFlow validates the API to ensure that mandatory elements are in place, such as permissions, template, date formats, that any specified device exists in AFA, and so on. Resource Name: ...",t:"Update a traffic change request\u0027s custom fields"},"485":{i:0.000783450081704854,u:"../Content/api-guide/Data-Types_3.htm",a:"Data types customFields Type",t:"Data types"},"486":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/actionInformation-Type.htm",a:"actionInformation Type    ",t:"actionInformation Type"},"487":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/objectchangerequestdetails_type.htm",a:"ObjectChangeRequestDetails Type",t:"ObjectChangeRequestDetails Type"},"488":{i:0.000985794992799579,u:"../Content/api-guide/response_type.htm",a:"Response Type",t:"Response Type"},"489":{i:0.00056709724466673,u:"../Content/api-guide/BusinessFlow-REST-Web-Services.htm",a:"BusinessFlow REST Web Services The BusinessFlow Web Services API supports BusinessFlow remote operations.  ",t:"BusinessFlow REST Web Services"},"490":{i:0.000524867751358075,u:"../Content/api-guide/Requests_2.htm",a:"The base URL for all REST requests is the following: https://\u003calgosec_server\u003e/BusinessFlow/rest/v1 where \u003calgosec_server\u003e is the BusinessFlow server URL. Some of the requests provided in this API are restricted for users with specific permissions. See BusinessFlow Permissions (see  BusinessFlow ...",t:"Requests"},"491":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/Swagger.htm",a:"The BusinessFlow REST API includes Swagger support. Swagger provides descriptions of every REST request and the ability to make simplified API request calls. You can access Swagger at https://\u003cASMS IP ADDRESS\u003e/BusinessFlow/swagger-ui.html.  You must be logged into BusinessFlow to access the Swagger ...",t:"Swagger"},"492":{i:0.000747937625541726,u:"../Content/api-guide/Logging-In_1.htm",a:"To perform many requests, you can authenticate with an authentication cookie. You obtain the cookie with the method described below.  Every request must be in JSON format. Each request must include the content-type header with the value application/json. Note: If you are using a development platform ...",t:"Logging In"},"493":{i:0.000524867751358075,u:"../Content/api-guide/Logging-Out_1.htm",a:"Logging Out If you obtained an authentication cookie by logging in, you can nullify it with the following method. Resource Name: /logout Request Method: POST Response:",t:"Logging Out"},"494":{i:0.000524867751358075,u:"../Content/api-guide/Error-Codes.htm",a:"When errors occur, a JSON status object and an HTTP status code are returned. HTTP Status codes: 200 - When returning a correct result of an empty set. 404 - When an object is not found or the address is incorrect. 403 - When the user used for authentication does not have permissions to view a ...",t:"Error Codes"},"495":{i:0.000524867751358075,u:"../Content/api-guide/applications.htm",a:"/applications The following are requests for application related resources. The base URL for applications is /BusinessFlow/rest/v1/applications.",t:"/applications"},"496":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/GET.htm",a:"GET / Returns a list of all applications. Return: Array of Application (see  Application )",t:"GET /"},"497":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/GET-id.htm",a:"GET /{id} Returns a single application revision. Parameters: id - The application revision ID. Return: Application (see  Application )",t:"GET /{id}"},"498":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/GET-id-application_id-revisions.htm",a:"GET /id/{application_id}/revisions Returns all revisions for the application ID. Parameters: application_id - The application ID. Return: Array of ApplicationRevision (see  ApplicationRevision )",t:"GET /id/{application_id}/revisions"},"499":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/GET-id-application_id.htm",a:"GET /id/{application_id} Returns the latest revision for the application ID. Parameters: application_id - The application ID. Return: Application (see  Application )",t:"GET /id/{application_id}"},"500":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/GET-id-authorized_users_and_roles.htm",a:"Gets lists of users and roles that are permitted to view and/or edit a specific application. Resource Name: /applications/{id}/authorized_users_and_roles Permissions Required: administrator Request URL Parameters: Return: Return Example: {   \"applicationName\": \"DNS\",   \"usersView\": [     ...",t:"GET /{id}/authorized_users_and_roles"},"501":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/GET-id-change_requests.htm",a:"GET /{id}/change_requests Returns a list of change requests for an application revision. Parameters: id - The application revision ID. Return: Array of ChangeRequest (see  ChangeRequest )",t:"GET /{id}/change_requests"},"502":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/GET-id-contacts.htm",a: